sQuestion: Tim had 12 marbles and he received 18 more from his friend. If he gave away 7 marbles, how many marbles does he have now?
Laura received 45 books for her birthday and bought 30 more during a sale. If she donated 20 books, how many books does she have now?
Daisy had 22 donuts, and she bought 24 more donuts. If she ate 6 of them, how many donuts does she have left?
A pet store had 5 goldfish and 15 guppies. During a sale they sold 13 fish. How many fish do they have left?
Thomas had 19 markers and bought 14 more. If he lost 12 of them, how many markers does he have now?
Grace collected 12 shells at the beach and another 25 from a gift shop. If she gave away 9 shells, how many shells does she have now?
Dennis bought 25 candies from a store and received 30 more at a party. If he ate 17 of them, how many candies does he have left?
A library had 4 science books and 10 literature books. If 8 of these books were borrowed, how many books are left in the library?
In a game, Sarah scored 15 points in the first round and 18 points in the second round. If she lost 6 points in the final round, how many points does she have in total?
At the art show Bill sold 23 drawings and then displayed 11 more. If Bill sold 5 drawings later, how many drawings does he have on display now?
Dan picked 3 apples and 9 oranges from the orchard. If he gave away 10 of the fruits, how many fruits does Dan have now?
John found 28 seashells on the beach and his brother found 32 more. If they gave away 11 seashells to their friends, how many seashells do they have in total?
A sandwich shop sold 21 veggie sandwiches and 33 turkey sandwiches. If they had to substitute ingredients for 9 sandwiches, how many proper sandwiches did they sell?
Lily bought 7 pens and 15 pencils from the store. If she lost 5 of them, how many pens and pencils does she still have?
Jill collected 22 rare coins and her friend gave her 18 more. If she lost 12 coins while moving, how many rare coins does she still have?
A classroom had 18 new books and 24 used books. If 8 books went missing, how many books are left in the classroom?
Adam saved up 3 dollars and then received another 5 dollars from his parents. If he spent 6 dollars on a toy, how much money does he have now?
Gina planted 28 sunflower seeds and 18 rose seeds in her garden. If she used 11 of them for a science project, how many seeds are left in the garden?
Michael bought 20 toy cars and was given 15 more by his brother. If he lost 8 toy cars while playing, how many does he have now?
Tracy baked 10 cupcakes and her sister baked 20 more. If they ate 6 of the cupcakes, how many cupcakes do they have left?
At a market stall, Linda sold 38 paintings and 22 posters. If she gave away 11 posters as gifts, how many items did she actually sell?
A library added 6 new science books and 15 magazines to its collection. If 5 of the magazines were lost, how many new items does the library have?
Jenny bought 24 chocolate bars and 16 candy sticks. If she shared 8 candy sticks with her friends, how many chocolates and candies does she still have?
Oliver received 16 gifts on his birthday and another 10 gifts from relatives. If he lost 7 gifts, how many does Oliver have now?
Nora had 20 pencils and found 11 more. If she lost 6 of them, how many pencils does Nora have now?
Lisa had 14 dolls and then bought 23 more. If she gave away 5 dolls, how many dolls does she have now?
Bob found 18 old stamps and then received 22 new ones from his uncle. If he lost 10 stamps, how many does Bob have now?
Harry saved 35 dollars from his allowance and earned 25 more from a part-time job. If he spent 14 dollars, how much money does he have now?
At a yard sale, Martin sold 7 toy cars and 21 action figures. If he gave away 10 of the toys, how many toys did he actually sell?
At a fundraising event, Tara baked 32 cookies and 25 brownies. If she gave away 10 brownies, how many baked goods does she have left?
